- Stand close. - 1, 2, 3.

108
00:09:55,431 --> 00:09:56,531
My gosh.

109
00:09:57,531 --> 00:09:59,860
- My gosh, come on. - Give me a proper pose.

110
00:10:00,001 --> 00:10:02,600
- Let's try one more time. - Hey, let's take a proper photo.

111
00:10:02,830 --> 00:10:05,740
Here we go. 1, 2, 3.

112
00:10:27,460 --> 00:10:30,090
Soo Ho's going back to the States tonight.

113
00:10:42,570 --> 00:10:44,041
(Bicycle Crossing)

114
00:11:00,061 --> 00:11:01,120
Taxi!

115
00:11:02,590 --> 00:11:03,661
Taxi!

116
00:11:09,131 --> 00:11:10,200
My gosh.

117
00:11:19,781 --> 00:11:22,651
Soo Ho! Soo Ho!

118
00:11:24,411 --> 00:11:26,251
Are you gone already?

119
00:11:27,651 --> 00:11:28,950
You jerk.

120
00:11:29,620 --> 00:11:32,490
Why did you come back if you were going to leave?

121
00:11:32,921 --> 00:11:34,791
Why did you follow me around?

122
00:11:37,291 --> 00:11:38,360
My gosh.

123
00:11:41,730 --> 00:11:42,801
Ju Kyung.

124
00:11:47,271 --> 00:11:48,370
Don't go.

125
00:11:56,811 --> 00:11:59,551
Please don't go.

126
00:11:59,551 --> 00:12:01,251
I won't let you go.

127
00:12:01,251 --> 00:12:02,921
So please don't leave.

128
00:12:06,391 --> 00:12:09,090
I'm not going anywhere.

129
00:12:10,891 --> 00:12:12,261
Don't you dare.

130
00:12:15,370 --> 00:12:16,570
So don't cry.

131
00:12:28,210 --> 00:12:31,251
- Don't go. - I won't.

132
00:12:35,190 --> 00:12:36,891
I didn't show it,

133
00:12:37,391 --> 00:12:39,460
but I was insanely nervous.

134
00:12:40,791 --> 00:12:42,690
- About what? - That you'd refuse...

135
00:12:44,330 --> 00:12:45,901
to see me.

136
00:12:45,901 --> 00:12:46,960
Liar.

137
00:12:48,370 --> 00:12:49,470
It's true.

138
00:12:51,501 --> 00:12:53,171
You were planning to leave today.

139
00:12:53,470 --> 00:12:54,501
What do you mean?

140
00:12:54,811 --> 00:12:57,271
I heard you were going back to the US tonight.

141
00:12:57,740 --> 00:12:58,811
Why would I?

142
00:12:59,110 --> 00:13:00,480
What's with your luggage?

143
00:13:01,080 --> 00:13:02,551
I was unpacking.

144
00:13:02,881 --> 00:13:05,751
What do you mean? Seo Jun said you were going back...

145
00:13:07,551 --> 00:13:08,791
He said that?

146
00:13:14,761 --> 00:13:15,891
Well...

147
00:13:16,031 --> 00:13:18,161
Did you run over here thinking I was leaving?

148
00:13:19,401 --> 00:13:21,401
- No, that's not it. - To stop me?

149
00:13:22,470 --> 00:13:23,931
That's not it.

150
00:13:24,131 --> 00:13:25,901
Ju Kyung. Ju Kyung!

151
00:13:30,840 --> 00:13:32,740
- Why are you running away? - I am not.

152
00:13:32,840 --> 00:13:33,980
Didn't you come to see me?

153
00:13:34,411 --> 00:13:37,710
I have to go home. It's very important.

154
00:13:38,320 --> 00:13:39,751
That's not the way.

155
00:13:43,521 --> 00:13:44,791
I'll take you home.

156
00:13:50,291 --> 00:13:51,330
Do you hate me?

157
00:13:53,061 --> 00:13:54,631
Won't you let me see your face?

158
00:13:54,970 --> 00:13:56,700
You were coming back anyway.

159
00:13:57,470 --> 00:13:59,100
You came back anyway.

160
00:14:01,940 --> 00:14:03,440
So why did you do that?

161
00:14:04,671 --> 00:14:06,110
Because it would be...

162
00:14:08,411 --> 00:14:09,881
too hard for you to wait.

163
00:14:11,011 --> 00:14:13,051
It was much harder...

164
00:14:14,521 --> 00:14:16,151
than waiting.

165
00:14:28,401 --> 00:14:29,671
It was...

166
00:14:32,100 --> 00:14:33,641
so hard for me too.

167
00:14:36,340 --> 00:14:37,710
That's why...

168
00:14:39,440 --> 00:14:42,051
I was looking for a way to come back.

169
00:14:42,811 --> 00:14:44,751
Even if my dad didn't wake up,

170
00:14:47,281 --> 00:14:49,021
I would've come back to you.

171
00:14:49,490 --> 00:14:51,891
What if I had gotten over you?

172
00:14:52,291 --> 00:14:53,761
I would've followed you around.

173
00:14:55,590 --> 00:14:57,061
What if I still said no?

174
00:14:57,561 --> 00:14:59,460
I would've cried and begged,

175
00:15:00,561 --> 00:15:02,031
and tried to seduce you.

176
00:15:04,531 --> 00:15:05,600
Ju Kyung.

177
00:15:07,771 --> 00:15:08,870
Please look at me.

178
00:15:11,271 --> 00:15:12,811
I'm sorry for making you...

179
00:15:16,411 --> 00:15:17,480
suffer.

180
00:15:18,251 --> 00:15:19,480
Why are you sorry?

181
00:15:22,590 --> 00:15:23,850
I know how you felt.

182
00:15:24,860 --> 00:15:28,291
I do, but seeing you again,

183
00:15:29,690 --> 00:15:32,131
I'm reminded of how much it hurt.

184
00:15:32,131 --> 00:15:33,431
I'm sorry for hurting you.

185
00:15:33,431 --> 00:15:35,200
You were hurting too.

186
00:15:35,870 --> 00:15:38,840
It must've been so hard in that faraway land.

187
00:15:39,671 --> 00:15:41,641
You had no other family.

188
00:15:42,771 --> 00:15:45,710
You were in the hospital alone, unable to do anything.

189
00:15:46,041 --> 00:15:47,710
It must've hurt so much.

190
00:15:48,781 --> 00:15:51,681
I was so worried, that I wanted to fly over, but...

191
00:15:54,921 --> 00:15:57,651
An 18-year-old has no money.

192
00:16:07,561 --> 00:16:09,031
We were too young,

193
00:16:10,370 --> 00:16:12,141
- weren't we? - Yes.

194
00:16:13,600 --> 00:16:14,700
Don't cry.

195
00:16:16,271 --> 00:16:17,271
Come here.

196
00:16:23,151 --> 00:16:24,950
It's shocking enough that they were dating.

197
00:16:24,950 --> 00:16:26,751
It's amazing that they're getting married.

198
00:16:27,450 --> 00:16:31,521
I know. Who else could handle my sister other than Mr. Han?

199
00:16:40,301 --> 00:16:41,401
What are you staring at?

200
00:16:42,131 --> 00:16:44,631
What? It's just...

201
00:16:45,700 --> 00:16:47,570
you've changed a lot.

202
00:16:48,440 --> 00:16:49,840
You even drive now.

203
00:16:56,580 --> 00:16:58,521
I still have this too.

204
00:17:00,021 --> 00:17:01,251
You didn't throw it away.

205
00:17:05,620 --> 00:17:06,691
We're the same.

206
00:17:07,961 --> 00:17:08,991
What?

207
00:17:09,630 --> 00:17:11,031
We haven't changed...

208
00:17:12,360 --> 00:17:13,531
from before.

209
00:17:16,870 --> 00:17:18,170
From before, when?

210
00:17:18,741 --> 00:17:20,001
When you were a crybaby?

211
00:17:20,640 --> 00:17:22,241
I cried once. Stop calling me a crybaby.

212
00:17:22,870 --> 00:17:24,511
You really are a crybaby.

213
00:17:26,610 --> 00:17:28,511
Why didn't you tell me sooner?

214
00:17:29,350 --> 00:17:31,781
I wouldn't have known if I didn't see the writing on the wall.

215
00:17:31,850 --> 00:17:35,350
I wanted to tell you on a special day, but couldn't.

216
00:17:36,551 --> 00:17:38,051
You should've just told me.

217
00:17:39,090 --> 00:17:42,360
I liked you when I was a kid too.

218
00:17:44,761 --> 00:17:46,860
I used to wait for you at the comic book store every day.

219
00:17:48,670 --> 00:17:50,471
I guess it wasn't one-sided...

220
00:17:51,570 --> 00:17:53,001
if you remembered me.

221
00:17:54,701 --> 00:17:55,811
I didn't like you.

222
00:17:56,471 --> 00:17:58,981
I only remember you as the comic book store crybaby.

223
00:18:00,981 --> 00:18:04,180
That's sad. I guess it was an unrequited love.

224
00:18:07,051 --> 00:18:08,691
How do you feel? Are you still sick?

225
00:18:09,090 --> 00:18:10,350
What do you mean?

226
00:18:11,590 --> 00:18:13,061
I wasn't sick.

227
00:18:13,291 --> 00:18:15,860
You ended up in the ER. How's your constipation?

228
00:18:17,991 --> 00:18:19,231
It's fine.

229
00:18:19,430 --> 00:18:22,070
You should exercise often and eat a lot of fiber.

230
00:18:22,070 --> 00:18:24,130
You need probiotics and lots of water.

231
00:18:24,231 --> 00:18:26,570
You need to do that regularly so you don't get constipated...

232
00:18:26,600 --> 00:18:28,541
Hey. Must you kill the mood by talking about that?

233
00:18:28,811 --> 00:18:30,511
It's so embarrassing.

234
00:18:30,711 --> 00:18:32,880
It's because I've been under a lot of stress.

235
00:18:33,180 --> 00:18:36,011
People with active digestive systems are usually very active.

236
00:18:37,850 --> 00:18:40,350
Pull over. I'll walk home as a workout.

237
00:18:40,850 --> 00:18:43,221
Yes. Over there. You can drop me off there.

238
00:18:43,420 --> 00:18:44,491
Pull over there.

239
00:19:55,430 --> 00:19:57,330
- Hey. - Are you on your way home?

240
00:19:57,961 --> 00:20:00,130
Yes, I am.

241
00:20:00,261 --> 00:20:02,100
- Aren't you tired? - Not at all.

242
00:20:02,570 --> 00:20:04,570
Is it hard to talk because you're driving?

243
00:20:04,771 --> 00:20:06,670
- Want to call me when you get home? - No.

244
00:20:07,600 --> 00:20:08,711
It's fine.

245
00:20:11,041 --> 00:20:12,640
I want to keep hearing your voice.

246
00:20:17,080 --> 00:20:18,110
What are you doing tomorrow?

247
00:20:20,281 --> 00:20:21,281
Why?

248
00:20:21,420 --> 00:20:22,491
I want to go see you.

249
00:20:24,051 --> 00:20:25,360
It seems like a dream...

250
00:20:26,461 --> 00:20:28,320
that I can see you tomorrow.

251
00:20:29,090 --> 00:20:30,231
For me too.

252
00:20:45,397 --> 00:20:47,056
When you start the chorus,

253
00:20:47,056 --> 00:20:49,096
- give a drum roll. - Here.

254
00:20:49,096 --> 00:20:50,727
- To explode. - Yes.

255
00:20:50,727 --> 00:20:53,197
And here, the guitar...

256
00:20:53,197 --> 00:20:56,636
- Don't pause on D, go right in. - Go right in.

257
00:20:58,237 --> 00:21:00,207
Why did you have to come out right then?

258
00:21:01,677 --> 00:21:03,477
You made me look lame.

259
00:21:05,316 --> 00:21:07,447
- What do you mean? - Unbelievable.

260
00:21:10,647 --> 00:21:12,187
Today was my last chance, you know.

261
00:21:13,286 --> 00:21:16,457
What I didn't do two years ago... Telling her how I feel...

262
00:21:17,126 --> 00:21:18,227
and getting rejected.

263
00:21:20,026 --> 00:21:21,096
I finally got to do it.

264
00:21:49,026 --> 00:21:50,187
What are you doing here?

265
00:21:56,866 --> 00:21:58,267
I'm not busy today,

266
00:21:58,697 --> 00:21:59,997
so I'll let you say what you couldn't yesterday.

267
00:22:01,596 --> 00:22:04,806
I honestly don't know what to say.

268
00:22:04,866 --> 00:22:06,076
As if.

269
00:22:07,207 --> 00:22:09,576
It's already written all over your face.

270
00:22:10,306 --> 00:22:12,816
You've always been one to wear your heart on your sleeves.

271
00:22:13,316 --> 00:22:15,046
All I can say to you...

272
00:22:15,886 --> 00:22:18,217
is that I'm grateful and sorry.

273
00:22:19,056 --> 00:22:20,457
As if that's something to be sorry about.

274
00:22:21,786 --> 00:22:23,086
I was aware...

275
00:22:24,187 --> 00:22:25,556
that you weren't over Soo Ho.

276
00:22:27,556 --> 00:22:29,167
So don't be sorry.

277
00:22:30,227 --> 00:22:32,866
You had no room for me in your heart,

278
00:22:33,397 --> 00:22:35,306
but I tried getting greedy for once.

279
00:22:36,606 --> 00:22:37,737
I'm sorry.

280
00:22:37,907 --> 00:22:39,306
I'm the one who should apologize...

281
00:22:40,207 --> 00:22:42,106
for confusing you by telling you how I feel.

282
00:22:44,276 --> 00:22:46,046
You must want me to mean that,

283
00:22:46,517 --> 00:22:47,747
but that'd be ridiculous.

284
00:22:48,247 --> 00:22:49,687
I should at least tell you how I feel.

285
00:22:51,447 --> 00:22:54,457
Your brother once said to me...

286
00:22:55,056 --> 00:22:58,026
that getting rejected helps you to move on.

287
00:22:59,826 --> 00:23:02,427
Don't worry though. My debut is imminent,

288
00:23:02,897 --> 00:23:04,397
so I won't have time to think about you.

289
00:23:04,866 --> 00:23:06,136
I'll move on quicker than you think.

290
00:23:08,596 --> 00:23:11,267
Keep holding that expression though, and I'll go.

291
00:23:11,707 --> 00:23:14,407
- Should I? - Okay, let's finish our drinks.

292
00:23:14,876 --> 00:23:16,447
- It'll be on me. - Got it.

293
00:23:31,326 --> 00:23:32,397
Let's go.

294
00:23:35,397 --> 00:23:36,927
Are you playing me for a fool already?

295
00:23:38,167 --> 00:23:40,667
- Please let me go. - I'll bet all my aroma candles...

296
00:23:40,667 --> 00:23:42,566
on you having not-so-innocent intentions.

297
00:23:42,566 --> 00:23:43,636
What will you bet in return?

298
00:23:44,106 --> 00:23:45,836
Stop that already!

299
00:23:47,407 --> 00:23:48,846
What are you doing in that suit of yours?

300
00:23:48,977 --> 00:23:51,747
I wanted to practice walking Hee Kyung down the aisle.

301
00:23:51,747 --> 00:23:54,816
What for? She and Joon Woo will be doing that themselves.

302
00:23:54,816 --> 00:23:56,386
Breakfast is ready!

303
00:23:57,116 --> 00:23:58,217
Why though?

304
00:23:58,217 --> 00:23:59,917
A lot of couples do that these days.

305
00:24:00,017 --> 00:24:01,316
You're here again, Soo Ho?

306
00:24:01,457 --> 00:24:02,556
Did you sleep in again?

307
00:24:02,687 --> 00:24:05,356
You've been here almost every day for the past month.

308
00:24:05,356 --> 00:24:08,897
Why don't you just marry her instead?

309
00:24:10,197 --> 00:24:11,826
You must think you're immune to pain.

310
00:24:11,927 --> 00:24:13,937
It'll be nice to get it over with.

311
00:24:14,737 --> 00:24:16,267
I won't allow it so easily.

312
00:24:16,267 --> 00:24:17,566
When should I pick you up today?

313
00:24:18,267 --> 00:24:20,336
It's all right. You'll probably be too tired.

314
00:24:20,576 --> 00:24:21,636
I'll be fine.

315
00:24:22,106 --> 00:24:23,747
It's what I expected from you.

316
00:24:23,747 --> 00:24:25,677
Back is the man who is young, rich, and handsome.

317
00:24:26,116 --> 00:24:28,276
I envy how you don't have to work to earn money.

318
00:24:28,276 --> 00:24:30,147
Your CSAT should be what you only think about.

319
00:24:30,217 --> 00:24:31,917
I studied until after midnight last night.

320
00:24:31,917 --> 00:24:34,056
Nobody's more desperate than I am right now.

321
00:24:34,056 --> 00:24:36,257
As if Go Woon will wait until you get into college.

322
00:24:36,257 --> 00:24:38,227
Must you be so annoying, you jerk?

323
00:24:38,227 --> 00:24:39,897
You jerk? To your sister?

324
00:24:41,457 --> 00:24:43,566
Why do you keep acting like his brother-in-law?

325
00:24:43,826 --> 00:24:44,897
Now, dig in.

326
00:24:44,897 --> 00:24:45,997
Sure.

327
00:24:47,937 --> 00:24:49,066
(Move Entertainment)

328
00:24:49,066 --> 00:24:51,036
(New Idol Group Makeup Concept Contest)

329
00:24:52,707 --> 00:24:55,207
A makeup concept contest for a new idol group?

330
00:24:59,247 --> 00:25:02,316
Chen, filming has been pushed back a little.

331
00:25:02,886 --> 00:25:04,247
- Can you wait? - Sure.

332
00:25:04,586 --> 00:25:06,286
Just a second. Hello?

333
00:25:09,187 --> 00:25:12,457
Ju Kyung, are you and Seo Jun dating?

334
00:25:13,757 --> 00:25:14,826
No.

335
00:25:15,526 --> 00:25:18,296
Of course. I knew he had high standards.

336
00:25:18,836 --> 00:25:21,437
That's right. And because of his high standards,

337
00:25:21,437 --> 00:25:23,907
he'd never date just about anyone.

338
00:25:25,437 --> 00:25:26,507
Mist.

339
00:25:29,076 --> 00:25:30,207
Enough!

340
00:25:30,647 --> 00:25:33,417
I didn't know I was at a sauna. Go easy on it, will you?

341
00:25:46,326 --> 00:25:48,497
Why does she have to follow us everywhere?

342
00:25:48,626 --> 00:25:49,967
She only takes up room in the van.

343
00:25:49,967 --> 00:25:51,796
It's not like she does any work.

344
00:25:51,796 --> 00:25:53,836
She's an intern and needs to learn the ropes.

345
00:25:53,836 --> 00:25:56,836
I know, but why does it have to be on my time?

346
00:25:57,066 --> 00:26:00,237
Even professionals can't meet all my demands perfectly,

347
00:26:00,237 --> 00:26:04,076
so it annoys me to bits to have a rookie tail us.

348
00:26:04,346 --> 00:26:05,717
What a brat.

349
00:26:05,717 --> 00:26:08,076
I knew you'd be kind and understand.

350
00:26:09,987 --> 00:26:12,356
Then, since I'm hungry,

351
00:26:12,517 --> 00:26:14,086
get me a roll of gimbap.

352
00:26:14,687 --> 00:26:15,987
With cheese.

353
00:26:24,296 --> 00:26:26,066
I delivered dumplings in high school...

354
00:26:26,066 --> 00:26:27,536
and now I'm buying someone else's gimbap.

355
00:26:33,937 --> 00:26:35,947
Hurry up, will you?

356
00:26:36,046 --> 00:26:37,147
Sorry.

357
00:26:41,316 --> 00:26:43,816
Are you kidding me? Don't you know I hate cucumbers?

358
00:26:44,046 --> 00:26:45,816
You should've had them taken out.

359
00:26:46,517 --> 00:26:48,816
Sorry. I didn't know you disliked them.

360
00:26:49,457 --> 00:26:50,687
Should I buy you another?

361
00:26:50,856 --> 00:26:52,697
Just get in and pick the cucumbers out.

362
00:26:52,697 --> 00:26:53,897
I'm starving.

363
00:26:57,427 --> 00:26:58,497
What is it?

364
00:26:59,566 --> 00:27:00,897
Pick out the cucumbers for me.

365
00:27:01,497 --> 00:27:02,667
Do it yourself.

366
00:27:04,237 --> 00:27:06,677
Ju Kyung, I'm Chen.

367
00:27:07,106 --> 00:27:09,707
Must I spend my time picking out cucumbers?

368
00:27:09,707 --> 00:27:11,276
Do it yourself, darn it.

369
00:27:11,376 --> 00:27:12,816
You have hands, don't you?

370
00:27:12,816 --> 00:27:15,276
I didn't study makeup to pick out your cucumbers.

371
00:27:15,276 --> 00:27:16,717
How dare you abuse your power?

372
00:27:17,086 --> 00:27:19,187
Are you out of your mind?

373
00:27:19,187 --> 00:27:21,257
- Do you want to get fired? - I'd rather quit...

374
00:27:21,386 --> 00:27:22,626
than get fired by you,

375
00:27:22,626 --> 00:27:24,457
you obnoxious brat!

376
00:27:24,457 --> 00:27:26,957
What? How dare you!

377
00:27:26,957 --> 00:27:28,497
Why? What's going on?

378
00:27:29,767 --> 00:27:32,667
- It's her. - Seriously?

379
00:27:32,667 --> 00:27:34,397
Who do you think you are?

380
00:27:34,937 --> 00:27:36,306
What did you do to her?

381
00:27:36,707 --> 00:27:38,036
That's enough!

382
00:27:38,036 --> 00:27:39,177
Chen, you too.

383
00:27:39,177 --> 00:27:40,576
Stop playing the victim, darn it.

384
00:27:40,576 --> 00:27:42,306
You must be out of your mind.

385
00:27:42,647 --> 00:27:44,407
What did you just say?

386
00:27:44,407 --> 00:27:45,507
Hey.

387
00:27:48,987 --> 00:27:51,217
Who are you laying hands on, you thug?

388
00:27:52,217 --> 00:27:53,286
Kang Soo Jin?

389
00:27:55,116 --> 00:27:56,227
Are you all right?

390
00:27:56,957 --> 00:27:58,126
Are you hurt?

391
00:28:02,626 --> 00:28:03,826
Have you been well?

392
00:28:05,126 --> 00:28:06,296
I guess.

393
00:28:07,437 --> 00:28:09,366
What about you? How have you been?

394
00:28:10,007 --> 00:28:11,306
After dropping out of school,

395
00:28:11,606 --> 00:28:13,576
Mom and I went to stay with my aunt overseas.

396
00:28:14,177 --> 00:28:15,876
My parents got divorced, you see.

397
00:28:16,076 --> 00:28:17,776
You must be attending college then.

398
00:28:18,106 --> 00:28:21,447
No, I've been doing volunteer work overseas.

399
00:28:22,017 --> 00:28:24,046
I only recently got back from Haiti.

400
00:28:24,417 --> 00:28:25,717
I see.

401
00:28:27,417 --> 00:28:28,616
No wonder.

402
00:28:29,757 --> 00:28:33,326
No one had heard from you, so I got curious.

403
00:28:33,457 --> 00:28:35,056
That's because I never told anyone.

404
00:28:36,267 --> 00:28:38,197
Now that I'm back, I wanted to apologize to you.

405
00:28:38,897 --> 00:28:41,467
It's why I asked around to figure out where you worked.

406
00:28:42,536 --> 00:28:43,667
Ju Kyung,

407
00:28:44,767 --> 00:28:45,806
I'm sorry.

408
00:28:47,276 --> 00:28:48,776
I'm sorry it took me so long to apologize.

409
00:28:52,417 --> 00:28:53,677
I'm really sorry.

410
00:28:55,017 --> 00:28:56,747
This isn't so that you'd forgive me.

411
00:28:57,046 --> 00:28:58,116
Soo Jin...

412
00:28:58,116 --> 00:29:00,187
I must've been a mess back then.

413
00:29:01,116 --> 00:29:03,386
It seemed like you had what I couldn't have,

414
00:29:04,786 --> 00:29:06,657
so I felt like I lost again.

415
00:29:07,096 --> 00:29:09,796
Stealing what you had and stomping on your relationship...

416
00:29:10,497 --> 00:29:12,227
seemed like a way of winning.

417
00:29:13,836 --> 00:29:15,866
I always had to be on top of everyone.

418
00:29:17,036 --> 00:29:18,437
That's what I was taught.

419
00:29:20,677 --> 00:29:23,647
Getting away from my father finally let me see...

420
00:29:24,507 --> 00:29:26,846
how deeply I hurt you back then...

421
00:29:29,286 --> 00:29:30,687
and what I had lost.

422
00:29:32,657 --> 00:29:34,086
I regretted my actions...

423
00:29:34,657 --> 00:29:36,886
and tried to apologize to you,

424
00:29:38,556 --> 00:29:40,826
but it didn't seem right to say over the phone.

425
00:29:42,197 --> 00:29:44,326
I also thought you'd ignore my calls too.

426
00:29:46,096 --> 00:29:47,397
You should've called.

427
00:29:49,536 --> 00:29:51,566
I would've loved to hear from you.

428
00:29:54,576 --> 00:29:55,876
Maybe I should've.

429
00:30:02,987 --> 00:30:04,286
I'm all right.

430
00:30:05,647 --> 00:30:07,286
It doesn't faze me anymore.

431
00:30:09,257 --> 00:30:10,657
Those memories...

432
00:30:11,727 --> 00:30:13,957
don't hurt me as much anymore.

433
00:30:15,796 --> 00:30:17,826
I guess that's why I don't even hate you.

434
00:30:19,536 --> 00:30:23,306
Still, I'm glad that I was able to see you...

435
00:30:24,167 --> 00:30:26,007
and apologize in person.

436
00:30:27,007 --> 00:30:28,776
I'm happier for you, you know.

437
00:30:29,346 --> 00:30:30,806
You're free now.

438
00:30:31,907 --> 00:30:33,376
Your hands have healed as well.

439
00:30:36,886 --> 00:30:38,017
They're pretty.

440
00:30:40,886 --> 00:30:41,917
I know.

441
00:30:45,526 --> 00:30:47,697
Your kick is still just as threatening.

442
00:30:47,697 --> 00:30:49,427
I let my temper get the best of me.

443
00:30:49,927 --> 00:30:52,066
I hope I didn't make things worse for you.

444
00:30:52,066 --> 00:30:54,997
All they can do is fire me anyway, so I'm good.

445
00:30:59,336 --> 00:31:00,836
- That song? - Of course.

446
00:31:01,237 --> 00:31:02,376
It was my personal choice.

447
00:31:02,707 --> 00:31:04,647
I've been a fan of Leo's songs for a very long time.

448
00:31:05,106 --> 00:31:06,977
You and Se Yeon made that song together.

449
00:31:07,316 --> 00:31:09,816
And I think it'd be meaningful to let Seo Jun sing it.

450
00:31:10,187 --> 00:31:12,987
Don't you feel bad about leaving it as a plagiarized song?

451
00:31:13,187 --> 00:31:14,457
I'm sure you're upset about it too.

452
00:31:18,126 --> 00:31:19,257
Why are you so serious?

453
00:31:19,697 --> 00:31:21,227
I just can't believe it.

454
00:31:21,856 --> 00:31:23,667
I've never studied music.

455
00:31:24,197 --> 00:31:26,237
The only lessons I got were from Se Yeon.

456
00:31:26,267 --> 00:31:27,997
Seo Jun already told me everything.

457
00:31:28,467 --> 00:31:30,306
He told me it's easy to tell how much you love music...

458
00:31:30,306 --> 00:31:32,136
judging by the instruments and equipment you own.

459
00:31:33,576 --> 00:31:36,276
If we don't like your song, we're not going to release it.

460
00:31:36,276 --> 00:31:37,977
So don't get too ahead of yourself.

461
00:31:40,447 --> 00:31:43,147
I want to hear Leo's version of "Missing You".

462
00:31:43,687 --> 00:31:45,286
Don't feel too pressured and just send us the song.

463
00:31:46,086 --> 00:31:47,217
Okay?

464
00:31:48,257 --> 00:31:50,257
Okay then. That's enough about work.

465
00:31:50,957 --> 00:31:52,626
Can I open my wedding gift?

466
00:31:53,356 --> 00:31:54,356
Sure.

467
00:31:55,697 --> 00:31:57,366
Why is it so heavy?

468
00:32:07,937 --> 00:32:09,677
You chose the best gift ever.

469
00:32:10,947 --> 00:32:12,106
Congratulations on your wedding.

470
00:32:12,276 --> 00:32:14,917
I have so many things to fix at home.

471
00:32:25,727 --> 00:32:28,556
I want to hear Leo's version of "Missing You".

472
00:32:30,497 --> 00:32:31,927
Passcode confirmed.

473
00:33:03,397 --> 00:33:07,667
The purple sky

474
00:33:09,736 --> 00:33:15,607
And the cool breeze makes me feel more lonely

475
00:33:17,107 --> 00:33:22,817
All the familiar memories

476
00:33:22,946 --> 00:33:28,986
Start coming back and remind me of you tonight

477
00:33:32,556 --> 00:33:36,826
I have so much to thank you for

478
00:33:39,067 --> 00:33:41,167
Our hearts used to flutter

479
00:33:41,596 --> 00:33:44,767
As we smiled at one another

480
00:33:44,866 --> 00:33:46,136
I fear

481
00:33:47,777 --> 00:33:48,937
Who's the guy? What's his name?

482
00:33:48,937 --> 00:33:51,047
Soo Jin already gave him a good kick in the face.

483
00:33:52,477 --> 00:33:54,846
I'm glad she did. If I were there, I would've beaten him...

484
00:33:54,846 --> 00:33:56,986
You wouldn't have beaten him to a pulp.

485
00:33:57,047 --> 00:33:58,647
Fortunately, I didn't get fired.

486
00:33:59,087 --> 00:34:00,857
But I am getting punished for it.

487
00:34:01,716 --> 00:34:03,926
I need to finish this. I'll call you back later.

488
00:34:10,527 --> 00:34:11,527
What are you doing?

489
00:34:12,497 --> 00:34:14,767
I'm washing the makeup brushes and sponges.

490
00:34:15,096 --> 00:34:16,506
You're doing it all alone?

491
00:34:18,636 --> 00:34:19,906
What are you doing?

492
00:34:20,337 --> 00:34:23,207
This is latex. If you wash it with hot water, it shrinks.

493
00:34:24,846 --> 00:34:25,946
I'm sorry.

494
00:34:27,277 --> 00:34:30,087
You need to divide them into natural and synthetic brushes first.

495
00:34:30,087 --> 00:34:32,517
You need to wash them differently, so don't get them mixed up.

496
00:34:32,917 --> 00:34:33,986
Okay.

497
00:34:34,687 --> 00:34:35,957
Was your name Lim Su Jeong?

498
00:34:35,957 --> 00:34:38,127
No, I'm Lim Ju Kyung.

499
00:34:38,127 --> 00:34:40,696
Were you the one who yelled at Chen earlier?

500
00:34:41,497 --> 00:34:43,196
I'm really sorry about that as well.

501
00:34:43,366 --> 00:34:44,997
I'm glad you did that.

502
00:34:45,596 --> 00:34:47,636
She looks down on our employees way too much.

503
00:34:48,636 --> 00:34:49,866
I told her to get her makeup done somewhere else.

504
00:34:50,667 --> 00:34:51,937
Director.

505
00:34:52,777 --> 00:34:54,036
About the makeup contest...

506
00:34:54,636 --> 00:34:57,377
for Move Entertainment's new idol group...

507
00:34:57,777 --> 00:34:59,047
Can I enter the contest as well?

508
00:34:59,277 --> 00:35:01,647
Ms. Lim Kyung Ja, can't you read?

509
00:35:01,877 --> 00:35:04,346
- Pardon? - It says all the employees...

510
00:35:05,017 --> 00:35:06,386
are allowed to enter. Didn't you see that?

511
00:35:07,817 --> 00:35:09,926
Thank you! I'll do my best!

512
00:35:12,187 --> 00:35:13,897
But my name is Lim Ju Kyung.

513
00:35:28,236 --> 00:35:30,346
Hey, look at him.

514
00:35:31,006 --> 00:35:32,506
He's so handsome. Who is she?

515
00:35:32,877 --> 00:35:35,076
- Do you think she's his girlfriend? - She's probably just a friend.

516
00:35:35,076 --> 00:35:36,216
Did I keep you waiting?

517
00:35:37,946 --> 00:35:40,417
Honey, what took you so long?

518
00:35:40,417 --> 00:35:41,716
I waited for you.

519
00:35:42,386 --> 00:35:44,056
Honey, did you eat?

520
00:35:44,357 --> 00:35:46,096
Here. Try a bite.

521
00:35:46,926 --> 00:35:48,826
- Let's get back to this. - She's his girlfriend.

522
00:35:55,567 --> 00:35:56,736
Did you just get jealous?

523
00:35:57,267 --> 00:35:59,777
Honey?

524
00:36:02,277 --> 00:36:03,747
I didn't get jealous.

525
00:36:04,576 --> 00:36:07,417
Don't go around with a smile on your face from now on, okay?

526
00:36:08,076 --> 00:36:11,047
I think those middle school kids made you get jealous.

527
00:36:12,116 --> 00:36:14,286
Honey.

528
00:36:14,357 --> 00:36:16,056
Cut it out, Soo Ho.

529
00:36:16,286 --> 00:36:18,786
Honey, why don't you try calling me "Honey" again?

530
00:36:18,926 --> 00:36:20,056
Forget it.

531
00:36:21,196 --> 00:36:23,196
- Should I give it a try? - Give what a try?

532
00:36:23,866 --> 00:36:25,196
Are you going to call me "Honey"?

533
00:36:26,497 --> 00:36:28,267
I haven't done a lot of makeup on guys,

534
00:36:28,267 --> 00:36:29,397
so I'm not used to it.

535
00:36:32,406 --> 00:36:34,636
- It tickles. - Stay still.

536
00:36:34,636 --> 00:36:35,877
Let me try this properly.

537
00:36:36,006 --> 00:36:38,977
It doesn't always come out the way I imagine it.

538
00:36:40,946 --> 00:36:42,176
You're a terrible model.

539
00:36:43,547 --> 00:36:45,216
- Soo Ho. - Okay, fine.

540
00:36:45,587 --> 00:36:46,687
Stay still.

541
00:36:47,486 --> 00:36:50,227
Okay, nice! I love it! 1, 2.

542
